<font color="#FF0000">COURAGE</font><br>
<tt>Fri Jan  3  9:21:43 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
As a professional, two things do stick in my mind: <br>
   1. The contempt we received from our &quot;privledged class.&quot;  Along with that was the added little goodies: while in Viet Nam, by wife would receive phone calls, telling her I was dead, and others telling her they hoped I would be killed or crippled.  Nice people.  Shows a lot of courage.<br>
         I remember. <br>
   2. Our abandonment of the South while the North crossed the DMZ in force. We wouldn't even send them ammo. More courage. Shameful affair.  My counterpart spent 16 years in a &quot;re-eduction&quot; camp, where 80% were starved and/or worked to death.<br>
         I remember.<br>
I wrote a littl ditty:<br>
                 Recent History<br>
       A study of recent history,<br>
            And events that have come to pass,<br>
       Shows that an allie who plays ball with the US<br>
           Ends up with the bat up his  axx.<br><br>
I do get a bit tired hearing of the &quot;courage&quot; of the protesters.  
